th-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"4 times 2, plus b, equals 5\"></span>, it follows that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"b equals negative 3\"></span>. Thus, an equation that defines the function <span class=\"italic\">f</span> is <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of x equals, a, raised to the 4 x minus 3 power\"></span>. It follows that the value of <span class=\"italic\">k</span> such that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of k equals, a, to the twenty ninth power\"></span> can be found by solving the equation <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"4 k minus 3, equals 29\"></span>, which yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"k equals 8\"></span>.</p>\n"
